  "text": "We also examined family size. Obesity is associated with infertility in men and women [CITATION_1] Diamanti-Kandarakis and Bergliele 2001) . Men who have no children in our study had a higher BMI than those who have children, while women's BMI was not different in the two groups. In the case of the former, this can in part be explained by the fact that obese infertile men have low level of serum steroid hormone binding globulin, total testosterone, and testosterone/estradiol ratio [CITATION_2] .",
